{"id":"46221583_Using_the_Velvet_de_novo_Assembler_for_Short-Read_Sequencing_Technologies","abstract":"The Velvet de novo assembler was designed to build contigs and eventually scaffolds from short-read sequencing data. This protocol describes how to use Velvet, interpret its output, and tune its parameters for optimal results. It also covers practical issues such as configuration, using the VelvetOptimiser routine, and processing colorspace data.","authors":["Daniel R Zerbino"],"meta":["September 2010Current protocols in bioinformatics / editoral board, Andreas D. Baxevanis ... [et al.] Chapter 11(5):Unit 11.5","DOI:10.1002/0471250953.bi1105s31","SourcePubMed"],"references":["40757824_Pebble_and_Rock_Band_Heuristic_Resolution_of_Repeats_and_Scaffolding_in_the_Velvet_Short-Read_de_Novo_Assembler","40696508_De_novo_assembly_of_human_genomes_with_massively_parallel_short_read_sequencing","40693352_The_Sanger_FASTQ_format_for_sequences_with_quality_scores_and_the_SolexaIllumina_FASTQ_variants","26275669_Genome_Project_Data_Processing_S_The_Sequence_AlignmentMap_format_and_SAMtools","24146276_ABySS_A_parallel_assembler_for_short_read_sequence_data","23571638_De_novo_fragment_assembly_with_short_mate-paired_reads_Does_the_read_length_matter","23444019_A_new_method_to_compute_K-mer_frequencies_and_its_application_to_annotate_large_repetitive_plant_genomes","5512383_ALLPATHS_De_novo_assembly_of_whole-genome_shotgun_microreads","275410466_The_Sequence_AlignmentMap_format_and_SAMtools","220263165_The_Sequence_AlignmentMap_format_and_SAMtools","19812531_Miller_SA_Dykes_DD_Polesky_HF_A_simple_salting-out_procedure_for_extracting_DNA_from_nucleated_cells_Nucleic_Acids_Res_16_1215","11839987_An_Eulerian_path_approach_to_DNA_fragment_assembly","5503854_Velvet_Algorithms_for_De_Novo_Short_Read_Assembly_Using_De_Bruijn_Graphs"]}